{"id": "4625", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4625", "title": "Animate Dead (priest)", "text": "Animate Dead is a 3rd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt;. It calls forth one or more skeleton warriors (depending on the game) who follows the caster's every command.\nIt is identical to its 5th level &lt;a href=\"Animate%20Dead%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;wizard counterpart&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell, revising its effects, undead creatures summoned, and description. See below:\nAnimate Dead\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Necromancy\nSphere: Necromantic\nRange: Medium\nDuration: 8 hours\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nThis spell causes a number of animated skeletons to rise up and serve the priest. The number and type of skeletons that appear depend upon the level of the cleric casting the spell.\n5th : 2 skeletons\n7th : 3 skeletons\n9th : 4 skeletons\n12th+ : 2 greater skeletons\nThe undead creatures will remain under the priest\u2019s control until they are slain, or the spell duration expires.\nSkeleton (2 Hit Dice):\nSTR 15, DEX 14, CON -, INT -, WIS 10, CHA 1; AL Chaotic Evil\nHP 24, AC 6, THAC0 18, Saving Throws 10/12/11/13/13\n1 Attack Per Round, 1d6+2 Crushing Damage (Mace +1)\nSpecial Qualities:\nImmune to charm, confusion, hold, poison, sleep, stun, &amp; death effects\nCold Resistance 100%\nSlashing &amp; Piercing Resistance 20%; Missile Resistance 40%\nGreater Skeleton (5 Hit Dice):\nSTR 16, DEX 14, CON -, INT -, WIS 10, CHA 1; AL Chaotic Evil\nHP 60, AC 4, THAC0 16, Saving Throws 9/11/10/12/12\n1 Attack Per Round, 2d6+2 Slashing Damage (Two-Handed Sword +1)\nSpecial Qualities:\nImmune to charm, confusion, hold, poison, sleep, stun, &amp; death effects\nCold Resistance 100%\nSlashing &amp; Piercing Resistance 40%; Missile Resistance 60%\nThis spell is only usable by Cleric/paladin classes."}
{"id": "16212", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16212", "title": "Animate Dead (wizard)", "text": "Animate Dead brings forth skeleton warrior(s) who follows the caster's every command.\nDescription.\nBG &amp; TotSC:\nBG2 &amp; after:\nGameplay.\nThe caster begins casting this spell, which takes 1 round to complete.\nThe player selects a location for the skeleton(s) to rise from the ground on the area map by using the selection cursor and clicking it.\nThe player can select a skeleton spawning map location up to 30 feet distance from the caster.\nWhen the spell is finished, the skeleton(s) rise from the selected spawning point, taking several seconds to do so before the creatures are able to receive orders and move.\nThe skeleton(s) have a duration of 8 hours before they expire.\nAs summoned creatures, they must conform to the various rules implemented in the game for this type of controlled creature, including the 5-summoned creature per area map limit.\nThe skeleton(s) cannot open doors or chests, interact with objects such as switches and control panels, nor do they clear the fog of war.\nThese creatures will remain in the area map where they were spawned and cannot transition to different area maps with the party.\nAnimated dead can be destroyed with a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Death%20Fog\"&gt;Death Fog&lt;/a&gt; and can be affected by both the party's and opponents &lt;a href=\"Turn%20Undead\"&gt;Turn Undead&lt;/a&gt; mechanics.\nThe caster's level determines the type of skeleton summoned. The game version can determine the number of animated dead summoned. See below for a summary:\nNotes.\nBG &amp; TotSC:\nWhere to obtain its scroll.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nTreasure\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced the arcane \"Animate Dead\" spell with \"Summon Shadow\". See below for description:\nSummon Shadow\nLevel: 5\nSchool: Necromancy\nRange: Long\nDuration: 3 turns\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nBy means of this spell, the caster summons a number of shadows, undead monsters which serve the mage under any conditions. The type and number of creatures that appear depend upon the level of the wizard casting the spell.\n9th : 3 shadows\n12th+ : 2 wraiths\nThe undead creatures will remain under the wizard\u2019s control until they are slain or the spell duration expires.\nShadow (3 Hit Dice):\nSTR -, DEX 14, CON -, INT 6, WIS 12, CHA 11; AL Chaotic Evil\nHP 36, AC 5, THAC0 13, Saving Throws 11/13/11/13/13\n1 Attack Per Round, 1d6+1 Cold Damage (Touch +1)\nCombat Abilities:\nChill Touch: creatures struck must save vs. death or lose 1 point of strength for 1 hour\nSpecial Qualities:\nImmune to normal weapons\nImmune to backstab, charm, confusion, hold, poison, sleep, stun, &amp; death effects\nCold Resistance 100%; Physical Damage Resistance 50%\nWraith (5 Hit Dice):\nSTR -, DEX 15, CON -, INT 11, WIS 13, CHA 12; AL Lawful Evil\nHP 60, AC 4, THAC0 12, Saving Throws 10/13/10/13/13\n1 Attack Per Round, 1d8+1 Cold Damage (Touch +1)\nCombat Abilities:\nLife Drain: each successful hit raises the wraith\u2019s hit points by 5 for 1 turn and causes the target to save vs. death or lose 1 level\nSpecial Qualities:\nImmune to normal weapons\nImmune to backstab, blindness, charm, confusion, hold, poison, sleep, stun, &amp; death effects\nCold Resistance 100%; Physical Damage Resistance 50%\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod, skeleton warriors are instantly destroyed by the &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Ability\"&gt;Psionic Ability&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Detonate\"&gt;Detonate&lt;/a&gt;, per the Advanced D&amp;D 2nd Edition ruleset."}
{"id": "8237", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8237", "title": "Anishai", "text": "Anishai is a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thief&lt;/a&gt; who works in &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var\"&gt;Mae'Var's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var%27s%20Guildhall\"&gt;Guildhall&lt;/a&gt;, despite her distrust of him. Even though she is a monk, she administers training and testing for guild members looking to improve or prove their lock-picking and trap detection ability.\nGameplay.\nThis female monk-thief-assassin is putting on the sex appeal and flirting like a professional. She wants to talk. Will you delve deeper?\nIf Mae'var's guildhall is ever hostile to the party, then you'll probably have to face her in battle. \nShe is capable of outputting more damage than one might expect, as there's an effect constantly applied to her that gives her +8 damage. She only inflicts non-lethal (subdual damage) rather than actual monk fist damage. If she manages to get a party member to zero HP they will fall unconscious.\nAnishai is scripted to use her potions for healing purposes and may apply an oil of speed at the beginning of combat.\nAnisha is not properly constructed to have all the requisite abilities of a level 10 monk. She has no extra powers or monk innate abilities at all, and none scripted for use. Her fighting animation does use monk fist blows and kicks. \nNotes.\nShe was given a Chaotic Neutral alignment in .&lt;br&gt;Her alignment was changed it to Lawful Evil in .\nMod content.\nMods:.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod doesn't revise much on this NPC. It provides a new default AI script for better tactical combat behavior. It however only adds 1 pip in single weapon fighting style and does not otherwise add the monk abilities she could have as a level 10 monk class. \nThe mod will have anishai quaff a potion at the outset of combat, which is random, such as a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Freedom\"&gt;Potion of Freedom&lt;/a&gt;.\nSCS get rid of the random treasure in her inventory and replaces it with a random scroll instead."}
{"id": "3373", "revid": "271925", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3373", "title": "Ankheg", "text": "Ankhegs are large (from 10' to 20' long) insectoid burrowing creatures. Strange chirping noises may be heard right before an Ankheg emerges to attack. It is generally recommended that low-level parties use extreme caution in areas where they are known to thrive, and to fight only one or two at a time. They generally attack very quickly, with either melee or ranged attacks, both of which contain acid and are easily capable of doing ~20 damage per hit. When one is killed, it will drop some high-quality treasure along with an &lt;a href=\"Ankheg%20Shell\"&gt;Ankheg Shell&lt;/a&gt;. The shells may be sold for a large sum, but transporting them poses significant difficulty, as each shell weighs 100 lbs.\nTactics.\nCombat.\nIt's risky to attack an ankheg with a character with low hitpoints.\n&lt;a href=\"Kagain\"&gt;Kagain&lt;/a&gt; at level 3 or 4 will have enough hitpoints to survive a hit from an Ankheg. He also has good saving throws.\nAnkhegs are especially vulnerable to the &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Sleep\"&gt;Wand of Sleep&lt;/a&gt; (usable by nearly any companion) and the mage spell &lt;a href=\"Sleep\"&gt;Sleep&lt;/a&gt;. The priest spell Command can help too.\nIf an ankheg is not asleep, beware its lethal ranged attack. &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt; allows a melee fighter to approach quickly. Having at least one backup fighter can help.\nTo inflict damage quickly on Ankhegs:\nOther party members can use ranged weapons such as bows.\nTo protect a tank melee fighter:\nShells.\nAssuming you find more than a few, there are two people you can sell them to - one within the city of Baldur's Gate (&lt;a href=\"Fenten\"&gt;Fenten&lt;/a&gt;), the other in Beregost (&lt;a href=\"Taerom%20Fuiruim\"&gt;Smith Taerom&lt;/a&gt;) offering the creation of a unique &lt;a href=\"Ankheg%20Plate%20Mail\"&gt;Ankheg Plate Mail&lt;/a&gt;, which in BG1 prevents any future sales of such shells to him (not in EE). In any case, you will have to haul the 100 lbs. stacks, which is when companions with high Strength can be really helpful, such as &lt;a href=\"Dorn%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Dorn&lt;/a&gt; (500 lbs), &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt; (320 lbs) and &lt;a href=\"Shar-Teel%20Dosan\"&gt;Shar-Teel&lt;/a&gt; (250 lbs). \nTo increase Strength and therefore carrying capacity:\nLastly, each character may carry 20% more than their maximum capacity and still stay mobile, albeit significantly slowed.\nIn you can have &lt;a href=\"Cromwell\"&gt;Cromwell&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt; fashion &lt;a href=\"Ankheg%20Plate%20Mail\"&gt;Ankheg Plate Mail&lt;/a&gt; from it for 5000.\nLocations.\nBaldur's Gate.\nThey are primarily found in the Farmland &lt;a href=\"Area%20North%20of%20the%20Friendly%20Arm\"&gt;Area North of the Friendly Arm&lt;/a&gt;, though will rarely appear on the outskirts of &lt;a href=\"Gullykin\"&gt;Gullykin&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Area%20North%20of%20Carnival\"&gt;Area North of Carnival&lt;/a&gt;. As with most mobs, they spawn in numbers proportional the strength of one's party. At lower levels a party should only encounter one per spawn, while a group averaging level 5 may encounter three, and only the most advanced parties will encounter more.\nBaldur's Gate II.\nThey will rarely appear in the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; area, but likely alone. Along with a higher level party, they're no longer such a significant threat.\nCorrupted Ankheg.\n A nest of six corrupted ankhegs can be found to the east of the great tree by some glowing crystals at the bottom of Resurrection Gorge during &lt;a href=\"Dorn%20II-Khan\"&gt;Dorn Il-Khan's&lt;/a&gt; quest."}
{"id": "12968", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12968", "title": "Ankheg Culling", "text": "Ankheg Culling is a quest given by &lt;a href=\"Gerde\"&gt;Gerde&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Fishing%20Village\"&gt;Fishing Village&lt;/a&gt; north of the &lt;a href=\"Friendly%20Arm%20Inn\"&gt;Friendly Arm Inn&lt;/a&gt;. It can be done at any time, but it may be best to wait until higher levels, as killing ankhegs can be challenging for low-level parties. For strategies on killing them effectively, see the &lt;a href=\"ankheg\"&gt;ankheg page&lt;/a&gt;. As hinted at by the dialogue, only the ankhegs in the northeast corner count for this quest.&lt;br&gt;\n You are asked to kill no more than ten ankhegs but it doesn't matter if you go over the quota.&lt;br&gt;\n You are asked to kill no more than four ankhegs and Gerde will only give you the reward if you don't go over. If you do, she'll be angry with you.\nOnce the party has killed one of those ankhegs, you can return to Gerde who will reward you with ."}
