{"id": "20411", "revid": "978785", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20411", "title": "Arbane's Sword +2", "text": ""}
{"id": "5210", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5210", "title": "Arbane's Sword of Agility", "text": "Arbane's Sword of Agility is an short sword +2. It has the usual bonus of +2 to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, speed and damage, but it also grants the wearer immunity to being &lt;a href=\"held\"&gt;held&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"paralyze\"&gt;paralyze&lt;/a&gt;d, and it can be used once a day to &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;haste&lt;/a&gt; the wielder for 12 seconds. The weapon has a weight of 2 lbs and it requires 5 strength to wield it. \nGameplay.\nThe protective equipped abilities granted by this item have some limitations. The sword does make the wielder immune to the &lt;a href=\"Held\"&gt;Held&lt;/a&gt; effect and or &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt;. However, some spells or innate abilities can't be completely blocked, such as the &lt;a href=\"Webbed\"&gt;Webbed&lt;/a&gt; effect or the &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt; effect. It could mean that the sword bearer is not paralyzed, but will have no ability to move (such as zero movement modifier). For example, a spider may trap you in its webbing, and you will have a web overlay animation on your party member, and can't move around the map, but you are still able to cast spells and otherwise fight and interact with the party member. It all depends on the internal coding of the particular spell effect."}
