{"id": "21644", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21644", "title": "Arcand the Mad", "text": "Arcand the Mad is a side &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; that appears in your &lt;a href=\"journal\"&gt;journal&lt;/a&gt; when you first speak to &lt;a href=\"Mad%20Arcand\"&gt;Mad Arcand&lt;/a&gt;. He has lost a &lt;a href=\"Discipliner\"&gt;cursed ring&lt;/a&gt; aboard a shipwreck to the west, which he cautions you not to wear yourself. Returning it to him will earn you 300 xp and an\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Fiery%20Burning\"&gt;Oil of Fiery Burning&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0potion.\nIf the ring is worn despite Arcand's warnings, the quest can be still be completed, because he will take the ring from the wearer without requiring a Remove Curse spell.\nIf you do not have a high enough &lt;a href=\"Reaction\"&gt;Reaction&lt;/a&gt;, he will show his extravagant nature:\nJournal.\nUpon accepting the quest:\nUpon completion:\nBugs.\nThe quest can be completed even without the required reputation by handing the ring to him, but you will not get the first journal entry and you wouldn't have a way to know that as you lack any skill in the Arcandian language (wertle wooo wooo).\nIf turning in the quest with a full inventory and the ring in the first inventory slot, the quest will be completed, the ring will be dropped on the ground, and no potion will be received, despite receiving the text that the ring was lost and the potion gained. This will prevent the exchange in the future, because the quest is marked complete. (Enhanced Edition v2.6.6.0)"}
