{"id": "5320", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5320", "title": "Arrow +2", "text": "Arrows +2 are flight &lt;a href=\"arrows\"&gt;arrows&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 &lt;a href=\"ammunition\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"bows\"&gt;bows&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 in the whole .\nStatistics.\nCompared with a normal &lt;a href=\"arrow\"&gt;arrow&lt;/a&gt;, the +2 aids the &lt;a href=\"Bows\"&gt;bowman&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;hitting&lt;/a&gt; their target, increasing the chance by 2. Regarding the basic &lt;a href=\"missile%20damage\"&gt;missile damage&lt;/a&gt;, however, in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\" these arrows are not different from regular ones, dealing 1 to 6 points of it; only in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate I&lt;/a&gt;\" the basic &lt;a href=\"damage\"&gt;damage&lt;/a&gt; is increased to 3 to 8 points.\nLike their counterpart &lt;a href=\"arrows%20%2B1\"&gt;arrows +1&lt;/a&gt;, this &lt;a href=\"ammunition\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; bears no &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchantment&lt;/a&gt; in \"\" (see &lt;a href=\"%23Bugs\"&gt;bugs&lt;/a&gt;), but counts as being enchanted with level 2 in the other .\nAs for other arrows, &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;s of all &lt;a href=\"class\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt; combinations, as well as &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;s, aren't able to use them. While &lt;a href=\"cavalier\"&gt;cavalier&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"kensai\"&gt;kensai&lt;/a&gt; also aren't allowed to fire a bow, they at least can help carrying some quivers of these \u2013 something, &lt;a href=\"monk\"&gt;monk&lt;/a&gt;s can only do in \"Baldur's Gate II\".\nThey are sold for a basic price of at the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;, but are worth only in &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tethyr\"&gt;Tethyr&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocations.\n\"Baldur's Gate\".\nAvailable through Algernon at &lt;a href=\"Feldepost%27s%20Inn\"&gt;Feldepost's Inn&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5226", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5226", "title": "Arrow +3", "text": "Arrows +3 are the most powerful of flight &lt;a href=\"arrows\"&gt;arrows&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 &lt;a href=\"ammunition\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"bows\"&gt;bows&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 without additional properties. They appear in the ', ' and the \"\" of the \"Shadows of Amn.\"\nStatistics.\nCompared with a normal &lt;a href=\"arrow\"&gt;arrow&lt;/a&gt;, the +3 aids the &lt;a href=\"Bows\"&gt;bowman&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;hitting&lt;/a&gt; their target, increasing the chance by 3. Regarding the basic &lt;a href=\"missile%20damage\"&gt;missile damage&lt;/a&gt;, however, in the \"Throne of Bhaal\" these arrows are not different from regular ones, dealing 1 to 6 points of it; only in the \"Siege of Dragonspear\" the basic &lt;a href=\"damage\"&gt;damage&lt;/a&gt; is increased to 4 to 9 points, similar as for &lt;a href=\"arrows%20%2B2\"&gt;arrows +2&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis &lt;a href=\"ammunition\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; counts as being &lt;a href=\"enchanted\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt; with a level of 3.\nAs for other arrows, &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;s of all &lt;a href=\"class\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt; combinations, as well as &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;s, aren't able to use them. While &lt;a href=\"cavalier\"&gt;cavalier&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"kensai\"&gt;kensai&lt;/a&gt; also aren't allowed to fire a bow, they at least can help carrying some quivers of these \u2013 something, &lt;a href=\"monk\"&gt;monk&lt;/a&gt;s can only do in \"Throne of Bhaal\"."}
