{"id": "30756", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30756", "title": "Arrow of Antimagic +1", "text": "An Arrow of Antimagic +1 is a found in .\nEffects.\nThese &lt;a href=\"enchanted\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt;\"(1)\" strike with a -1 bonus to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, but deal only 1 to 2 points of missile damage. If a target is hit, they suffer from an effect similar to &lt;a href=\"Miscast%20Magic\"&gt;Miscast Magic&lt;/a&gt; for the next five rounds, and with a chance of fifty percent, half the &lt;a href=\"spells\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt; cast during this period will fail. The effect bypasses the victim's potential &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, but a &lt;a href=\"save\"&gt;save&lt;/a&gt; vs. spell is allowed, with a -2 bonus for &lt;a href=\"abjurers\"&gt;abjurers&lt;/a&gt;. Subsequent hits don't add to the chance, but reset the duration of five rounds."}
{"id": "4259", "revid": "5653418", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4259", "title": "Arrow of Biting", "text": "Arrows of Biting are &lt;a href=\"ammunition\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"bows\"&gt;bows&lt;/a&gt; which inflict both &lt;a href=\"Physical%20damage\"&gt;Physical damage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; upon a successful hit.\nClassified as magical missile weapons, they can damage creatures immune to &lt;a href=\"IMMUNE1.ITM\"&gt;normal weapons&lt;/a&gt;, but not those immune to missiles. \nTypes.\nNormal type.\nWhen fired with a bow and hitting its target, the arrow will not only inflict 1 to 6 points of &lt;a href=\"missile%20damage\"&gt;missile damage&lt;/a&gt;, but also infiltrate the victim's bloodstream \u2013 unless a &lt;a href=\"save\"&gt;save&lt;/a&gt; vs. Death is made \u2013 with a nasty poison effect that causes additional &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; over a certain amount of time.\nThe in-game description reads \"\"Target must save vs death or lose 30% of its maximum hit points within 20 seconds\".\" However this description of \"percent-based\" damage is not accurate. The actual poison effect is 1 damage per second over 20 seconds, for a maximum of 20 \"flat\" poison damage. Nevertheless, this poison is still very effective for the purpose of interrupting enemy spellcasters. (Were the in-game description accurate, these arrows would be extraordinarily effective in &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Legacy of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt; mode, where enemies gain 3x base HP + 80 additional HP). \nA target's &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; doesn't block the poison, but in the \"Enhanced Editions\" it cannot be applied to , and creatures with at least 100% .\nThey are sold for a base price of only at the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;, but are worth in &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tethyr\"&gt;Tethyr&lt;/a&gt;.\nCreature Type.\nTwo variants of this ammunition exist in game, and the creature variant is only equipped by certain &lt;a href=\"creatures\"&gt;creatures&lt;/a&gt;. This variant can neither be pickpocketed or dropped.\n : Inflicts 5 points of poison damage per round for a maximum number of 10 rounds (up to 50 in total) in the original game and expansion.\n : Inflicts 1 point of damage every 5 seconds for a maximum of 60 seconds (up to only 12 in total) in all other ."}
{"id": "6351", "revid": "50866439", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6351", "title": "Arrow of Detonation", "text": "Arrows of Detonation are in the .\nGameplay.\nThe first unusual thing about these arrows is that as long as the intended creature is targetable then the arrow can be fired and automatically hit the target, regardless of its armor class.\nThe exception to this is if the target creature can only be hit with +2 enchanted items or greater.\nWhen fired with a &lt;a href=\"Bows\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt;, these deal &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; rather than &lt;a href=\"missile%20damage\"&gt;missile damage&lt;/a&gt;, to all in the blast radius. Though their original descriptions speak of additional 1 to 6 points &lt;a href=\"damage\"&gt;damage&lt;/a&gt;, this actually isn't dealt (see &lt;a href=\"%23Bugs\"&gt;bugs&lt;/a&gt;). Only in the \"Baldur's Gate: Enhanced Edition\", this &lt;a href=\"Physical%20damage\"&gt;physical damage component&lt;/a&gt; is added. \nThe explosion, however, is the same in all : 6 to 36 points of fire damage for all &lt;a href=\"creatures\"&gt;creatures&lt;/a&gt; within a radius of 15 feet around the target. &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can help avoid this damage completely, while a successful &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Spell \u2013 without any &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;specialist&lt;/a&gt; bonuses or penalties \u2013 will at least reduce it by half.\nThe fire damage applied to all creatures in the blast radius is coded as a &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 0 (zero) effect, thus ignoring spell level protections such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs non-&lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"ammunition\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt;, the arrows of detonation will not strike certain creatures immune to such, but are a guaranteed hit on any other, regardless of the bowman's &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; rating.\nThe Mustard Jelly form of &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20Self\"&gt;Polymorph Self&lt;/a&gt; takes no damage from arrows of detonation.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt; spell will not affect this arrow.\n&lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mantle\"&gt;Mantle&lt;/a&gt;, and similar spells will make the target unhittable by the missile.\nEnemy creatures do not utilize these arrows against the player in , except in one specific instance as part of &lt;a href=\"Rashad\"&gt;Rashad's&lt;/a&gt; questline in the portion of the game (Ref: OHROVIDI.cre)."}
{"id": "5343", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5343", "title": "Arrow of Dispelling", "text": "Arrows of Dispelling are (&lt;a href=\"ammunition\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"bows\"&gt;bows&lt;/a&gt; in the ) which will &lt;a href=\"dispel%20magic\"&gt;dispel magical effects&lt;/a&gt; from the target, while still inflicting &lt;a href=\"missile%20damage\"&gt;missile damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis arrow will apply a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect on any target that is successfully hit by it.\nThe effect will remove any and all dispellable effects regardless of the caster's level or &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; of the effect(s) - assuming the arrow struck a target, a text will display reading \"Dispel effects\" even if the target didn't have any effects on it.\nThe arrow can be quick way for a party member to dispel another ally's negative &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt;, if the arrow is able to hit them (although they may suffer missile damage).\nFor example, if a level 27 &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt; who is currently protected by &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Shield\"&gt;Spell Shield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Fire%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Protection From Fire (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; were struck successfully by this arrow - then the \"Stoneskin\" and \"Protection from Fire\" spell effects would be removed. The \"Spell Shield\" and \"Spell trap\" would remain, as those two are unaffected by Dispel Magic effects.\nThis arrow is a &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;Magical item&lt;/a&gt;, although it isn't technically an &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;Enchanted item&lt;/a&gt;. However, in terms of what a magical item can strike, it behaves the same as a +1 enchanted item. Therefore, it can strike an ordinary Lich, or a &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20Golem\"&gt;Flesh Golem&lt;/a&gt;, but if a target requires at least a +2 enchantment to hit it, then the arrow will be \"Weapon ineffective\" and be unable to strike the creature.\nFurther, the arrow will be blocked with a &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Mantle\"&gt;Mantle&lt;/a&gt; spells.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt; spell and the &lt;a href=\"Reflection%20Shield\"&gt;Reflection Shield&lt;/a&gt; will reflect/bounce this arrow back at the originator.\nThis arrow will remove/cure &lt;a href=\"Feeblemindedness\"&gt;Feeblemindedness&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Deafness%20effect\"&gt;Deafness effect&lt;/a&gt;, even if the effect is not dispellable."}
{"id": "3363", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3363", "title": "Arrow of Fire", "text": "Arrows of Fire, +2 in the ' and ', are \u2013 &lt;a href=\"ammunition\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"bows\"&gt;bows&lt;/a&gt; in the \u2013 which may inflict additional &lt;a href=\"fire%20damage\"&gt;fire damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn \"\", for all intents and purposes, they will behave like +1 weapons.\nStatistics.\nEnchantment, THAC0 and &lt;a href=\"damage\"&gt;damage&lt;/a&gt; for these arrows are somewhat inconsistent throughout the \"Baldur's Gate\" series. Only in the \"Baldur's Gate: Enhanced Edition\" and \"Siege of Dragonspear\", this ammunition for bows is &lt;a href=\"enchanted\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt;, and that at a level of 2 which is reflected in their name. Though missing this enchantment in other , all except the \"Baldur's Gate II: Enhanced Edition\" add a bonus of 2 to the bowman's &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;. The same bonus is applied to the arrow's &lt;a href=\"missile%20damage\"&gt;missile damage&lt;/a&gt; in the first game, while it deals only the basic 1 to 6 points in the second part. The additional fire damage, which a &lt;a href=\"save\"&gt;save&lt;/a&gt; vs. spell \u2013 without any &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;specialist&lt;/a&gt; bonuses or penalties \u2013 is allowed against and that can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, accounts for 1 to 6 points in \"Baldur's Gate I\", but \u2013 reduced, again \u2013 only for 1 to 2 points in \"Baldur's Gate II\".\nThese limitations come with a price, literally: the arrows are sold with a base value of at the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;, but are worth only in &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tethyr\"&gt;Tethyr&lt;/a&gt;."}
