{"id": "7250", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7250", "title": "Arrow of Slaying", "text": "Arrow of Slaying is bow launched missile available in both &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate (game)&lt;/a&gt; and and the Enhanced Editions. \nGameplay.\nThe arrow is bestowed with a massive &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus of 15 to hit a target.\nThese are categorized as magical items, and for all intents and purposes, they will behave like +1 weapons for the purposes of what they can strike.\nThe special feature of the arrow is to instantly slay &lt;a href=\"Ogre%20Mage\"&gt;Ogre Mage&lt;/a&gt; creatures, who get no saving throw and are instantly exposed to the &lt;a href=\"Slay\"&gt;Slay&lt;/a&gt; effect on a successful hit.\nTo other creatures the arrow deals 1d6 points of &lt;a href=\"Missile%20damage\"&gt;Missile damage&lt;/a&gt;. Due to its price, it would be an expensive ammunition to use upon anything else but an Ogre Mage.\nThe arrow's slay effect can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, although in an unmodified game the ogre mage doesn't have such protection, nor do any of their scripted spells provide any.\nNote.\n&lt;a href=\"Kahrk\"&gt;Kahrk&lt;/a&gt; is arguably the most dangerous Ogre Mage in the first game and is often a frustrating enemy for novice players. So, this arrow provides a sure-fire method to defeat this challenging adversary."}
