{"id": "22649", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22649", "title": "Artemis Entreri", "text": "Artemis Entreri will show up as a hostile creature in &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Lair\"&gt;Bodhi's Lair&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; if you have asked &lt;a href=\"Drizzt\"&gt;Drizzt&lt;/a&gt; for assistance and have his component enabled in &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business&lt;/a&gt; mod. \nHe carries a unique dagger called &lt;a href=\"Life-Stealer\"&gt;Life-Stealer&lt;/a&gt; which is a cut content of the main BG2 campaign but can be obtained in tier 4 store.\nGameplay.\nArtemis is invisible when spawned into the area - which is triggered by Bodhi's dialogue. His first attack will be a &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt; most probably. \nHe'll quaff a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invisibility\"&gt;Potion of Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; before attempting his next backstab - and then try and do it again.\nHis potions are used for self-healing when a HP loss trigger value is reached. He can try this twice, for additional staying power.\nCrossmod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod adds a new default fighter thief script to this creature for better backstabbing and targeting behavior. Weak and vulnerable targets are prioritized for attack - not necessarily the closest target to Artemis."}
