{"id": "4562", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4562", "title": "Ashen Scales", "text": "The Ashen Scales +2 are that can only be obtained if siding with the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt; of '. In addition, they can be purchased in '.\nGameplay.\nAshen Scales cannot be worn together with a number of other protective items, such as &lt;a href=\"rings\"&gt;rings&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"amulets\"&gt;amulets&lt;/a&gt; of protection.\nCompared to non-&lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; , this &lt;a href=\"armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; improves the wearer's &lt;a href=\"armor%20class\"&gt;armor class&lt;/a&gt; by two further points, setting it to 2 in general, while protecting against &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;piercing&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Missile%20damage\"&gt;missile&lt;/a&gt; attacks with a bonus of 1 and against &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;crushing&lt;/a&gt; with a bonus of even 2. It weighs less than the half of regular &lt;a href=\"splint%20mail\"&gt;splint mail&lt;/a&gt;, only 18 lb, but still requires the same &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; of 8 to be able to wear it.\nDespite being made from &lt;a href=\"wyvern\"&gt;wyvern&lt;/a&gt; scales, this armor is unusable by druids. \nIt can be worn by &lt;a href=\"barbarian\"&gt;barbarian&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt; except the &lt;a href=\"kensai\"&gt;kensai&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;, pure &lt;a href=\"ranger\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt; and all &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; classes. In addition, it is allowed for the &lt;a href=\"totemic%20druid\"&gt;totemic druid&lt;/a&gt; and \u2013 in the original ' only \u2013 the &lt;a href=\"avenger\"&gt;avenger&lt;/a&gt;, the latter being restricted from usage in the '.\nAs with other splint mail, &lt;a href=\"pickpocket\"&gt;pickpocket&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"stealth\"&gt;stealth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20spells\"&gt;casting wizard spells&lt;/a&gt; are disabled while wearing it."}
