{"id": "5642", "revid": "283586", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5642", "title": "Athkatla", "text": "Athkatla, also known as the \"City of Coin\", is the capital city of the nation of &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt;, on the continent of &lt;a href=\"Faer%C3%BBn\"&gt;Faer\u00fbn&lt;/a&gt;, ruled by the &lt;a href=\"Council%20of%20Six\"&gt;Council of Six&lt;/a&gt;.\nAthkatla is a city where almost anything is legal, though the &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizards\"&gt;Cowled Wizards&lt;/a&gt; impose strict laws that limit and/or prohibit the use of arcane magic, going so far as to require arcane magic-users to purchase licenses to cast spells within Athkatla. Anyone who breaks this law is sent to &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;, a special asylum for spellcasters (insane or otherwise) or individuals driven mad by magic-related afflictions; otherwise, they are killed on the spot if they resist."}
