{"id": "5785", "revid": "3983911", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5785", "title": "Athkatla City Gate", "text": ""}
{"id": "5784", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5784", "title": "Athkatla City Gates", "text": "The Athkatla City Gates is the exit point from &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; to other areas of &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nThis small area consists of one street with a single building to enter. It is necessary to walk through this area to exit the city and gain access to any area outside of Athkatla, at least the first time you traverse the World Map.\nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Check%20the%20Bodies%20%28CtB%29\"&gt;Check the Bodies (CtB)&lt;/a&gt; Mod and the \"Velvetfoot\" module will initiate in the Athkatla City Gates area if your PC is at least a level 10 Fighter Class, or is at least level 14 in another class. A Pirate will approach the party and have some bizarre statements for you to ponder.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; Mod will initiate a special cutscene and encounter in this area, after returning from the Underdark. The Mod asks if you wish to install this component. This encounter is an especially difficult ambush with potentially deadly consequences but high rewards as well. There are opportunities to talk your way out of it, but one misstep in dialogue could derail that. This encounter may be one of the most difficult battles encountered by the party in the saga up to and including Chapter 6. Find out and try the challenge by facing the \"Chosen of Cyric\" lead by the Assassin \"Venduris\". Unique loot rewards are available with a victory."}
{"id": "5763", "revid": "3983911", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5763", "title": "Athkatla Dock District", "text": ""}
{"id": "5647", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5647", "title": "Athkatla Docks", "text": "Athkatla Docks is an area in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". It is one of the seven districts of the city.\nDescription and gameplay.\nThe most notable place in the Athkatla Docks is the Shadow Thieves Guildhall, the main base for the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt;. Two returning characters can be found: &lt;a href=\"Xzar\"&gt;Xzar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Edwin%20Odesseiron\"&gt;Edwin&lt;/a&gt;. Xzar wants &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to help him free &lt;a href=\"Montaron\"&gt;Montaron&lt;/a&gt; from the Harpers, though he cannot be recruited. Edwin can be found in Mae'Var's Guild, and unlike Xzar he can be recruited.\nAt night, there are two \"spawn points\" in the area that may introduce various small groups of muggers/thieves out to kill the party for loot. They typically attack from the shadows while hidden/invisible, and attempt backstab attacks. If the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;SCS&lt;/a&gt; mod is installed they can try an attack, then quaff a potion of invisibility, and then try again, so beware.\nGuild War.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;chapters 2 and 3&lt;/a&gt;, there is a guild war going on between the Shadow Thieves who are led by &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt;, and the Vampires from the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Graveyard District&lt;/a&gt; who are led by &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;. The player must side with one of these belligerents and defeat the other's leader. Every night there are ambushes going on in the streets and the player would try to kill the opponent of the side they are on.\nIn earlier chapters you may witness these fights and perhaps pick a side, but they do not result into a definitive choice until chapter 3.\nContainers.\nThe district has four barrels, three crates and one chest that contain items; the rest are empty. At least one is fastened with a lock.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Tactics%20for%20BG2EE\"&gt;Tactics for BG2EE&lt;/a&gt; mod will place the \"Lich in the Docks\" encounter somewhere in the area."}
{"id": "5837", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5837", "title": "Athkatla Government", "text": "The Athkatla Government District is one of the seven districts in the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. This is where the nobles live and where the council of six, the rulers of Athkatla and &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt;, have meetings. \nWithin the district is &lt;a href=\"Jan%20Jansen\"&gt;Jan Jansen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Viconia%20DeVir\"&gt;Viconia DeVir&lt;/a&gt;, both of whom are potential &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;Companions&lt;/a&gt;. Jan can be hired by telling the guard he was not trying to sell illegal items. Viconia can be allowed to join simply by rescuing her from the stake to which she is bound. The fanatics are soon to set her afire. A disintrested Amnian guard seems not to care.\nHere also is the &lt;a href=\"Delryn%20Estate\"&gt;Delryn Estate&lt;/a&gt;, home of &lt;a href=\"Anomen%20Delryn\"&gt;Anomen Delryn&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Firecam%20Estate\"&gt;Firecam Estate&lt;/a&gt; where &lt;a href=\"Keldorn%20Firecam\"&gt;Keldorn Firecam&lt;/a&gt;'s family lives. "}
{"id": "5838", "revid": "3983911", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5838", "title": "Athkatla Government District", "text": ""}
{"id": "5670", "revid": "25646820", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5670", "title": "Athkatla Graveyard", "text": "The Athkatla Graveyard is an area in &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". It is one of the seven districts of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.\nDuring the day, there are people visiting their fallen relatives and those they loved who are no longer with them, and it is a peaceful place full of singing birds. During the night, however, the graveyard sees undead creatures walking around, most notably &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt;s.\nChapter 2.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt; of , you will receive an invitation to &lt;a href=\"Meeting%20with%20Valen%27s%20mistress\"&gt;meet with Valen's mistress&lt;/a&gt; by coming to the graveyard after dark.\nChapter 3.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt;, if you sided with the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt;, then you will have to go to the graveyard under &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt;'s orders and get rid of all the vampires there.\nChapter 6.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt;, you will have to come back to the graveyard (no matter who you sided with in Chapter 3) and defeat &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;, leader of the vampires.\nPotential companion.\nIf you saved &lt;a href=\"Viconia%20DeVir\"&gt;Viconia DeVir&lt;/a&gt; from being burned at the stake, but did not yet recruit her, she can be found within this district. If you dismiss her from the party, depending on the circumstances, she will await you again in this area."}
{"id": "5765", "revid": "3983911", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5765", "title": "Athkatla Graveyard District", "text": ""}
{"id": "5652", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5652", "title": "Athkatla Slums", "text": "The Slums is the poorest of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; districts during the campaign. It is the first and only district that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Party\"&gt;Party&lt;/a&gt; can travel to after exploring &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%201\"&gt;Chapter I&lt;/a&gt; of the game.\nChapter II.\nImmediately after entering the Slums for the first time, Gorion's Ward encounters Gaelan Bayle. This encounter is unavoidable. Gaelan claims to knows how to rescue &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt;, and will take the party to his home to propose a deal (for detail, see the page for &lt;a href=\"Gaelan%20Bayle\"&gt;Gaelan Bayle&lt;/a&gt;). After the deal is struck, a cut-scene plays, initiating &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter II&lt;/a&gt; of the game. In short, Gaelan's deal involves raising a large fee for the information to rescue Imoen, so he provides a few suggestions to get started. His nephew &lt;a href=\"Brus\"&gt;Brus&lt;/a&gt; then leads the party to the Copper Coronet, a nexus for those in need of the Ward's skills.\nSlaver guards.\nDirectly outside of the Copper Coronet at night is a lone &lt;a href=\"Slaver%20Guard\"&gt;Slaver Guard&lt;/a&gt;, who has very little to say, making one wonder why he is there. If you ask what he is doing or guarding he'll say \"This? It's an inn. Copper Coronet. Go in an' ask fer yerself\". He is a precursor for what is to come later. If you don't like his tone, or are just feeling frisky, you can put this scum down, with no repercussions. Later on, at a certain point there will be a late-night encounter (hour 22 until dawn). More Slaver Guards are seen dragging a prisoner-slave through the streets. If the party intervenes and frees the slave by killing the leading and trailing guards, they are awarded with . For more detail, see the page for &lt;a href=\"Slaver%20Guard\"&gt;Slaver Guard&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrade.\nEven if it seems that the Slums, being on the seedier side of town, would have a fence or three, there are none. Three of the five slums merchants hint at \"selling\" \"acquired\" goods, but they do not \"buy\" them. These include the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Market%20Thief%20%28Athkatla%20Slums%29\"&gt;Black Market Thief&lt;/a&gt; above the tavern, the &lt;a href=\"Storekeep%20%28Athkatla%20Slums%29\"&gt;Storekeep&lt;/a&gt; to the east, and the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thief&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Arledrian\"&gt;Arledrian&lt;/a&gt;, on the 2nd floor of &lt;a href=\"Gaelan%20Bayle%27s%20Home\"&gt;Gaelan Bayle's home&lt;/a&gt;. Inside the tavern, both &lt;a href=\"Bernard\"&gt;Bernard&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Joluv\"&gt;Joluv&lt;/a&gt; do legitimate business and have many useful items for sale. However, to fence, the party needs either go back to &lt;a href=\"Jayes\"&gt;Jayes&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;, or forward to the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20%28Temple%20District%29\"&gt;Temple Sewers&lt;/a&gt; to find alternatives.\nCopper Coronet.\nMost of the slums is dominated by the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;, a large tavern in the center of the district. Here, the party may buy, sell, rest, and recruit up to three more Potential Companions: &lt;a href=\"Anomen%20Delryn\"&gt;Anomen Delryn&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Korgan%20Bloodaxe\"&gt;Korgan Bloodaxe&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Nalia%20de%27Arnise\"&gt;Nalia de'Arnise&lt;/a&gt;.\nAsk around for work to accept a number of &lt;a href=\"Side%20quest\"&gt;side&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; quests to raise funds (see &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums%23Related%20Quests\"&gt;Related Quests&lt;/a&gt; below). The tavern is also a great launch point for taking on the &lt;a href=\"stronghold\"&gt;stronghold&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"quests\"&gt;quest(s)&lt;/a&gt; most appropriate to Gorion's Ward class(es). \nOn the roof of the tavern is a &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Ilmater%20%28Slums%20District%29\"&gt;Temple of Imater&lt;/a&gt; for restorative cures that are more demanding than simple rest can provide.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; mod changes the for-sale inventory slightly, adding mod-only items, and also converts them into \"fences\", allowing the sale of stolen goods.\nInstallation of &lt;a href=\"Ooze%27s%20Lounge\"&gt;Ooze's Lounge&lt;/a&gt; mod allows passage through the sewer grate in the slums to a new area with quests, a strange temple and new merchants. A key is needed to open it.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Pack\"&gt;Quest Pack&lt;/a&gt; mod adds content to the slums regarding a Money lender in the Copper Coronet and a woman named \"Moiya\" in the slums.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Dungeon%20Crawl\"&gt;Dungeon Crawl&lt;/a&gt; mod adds a necessary questline encounter with the \"Shadow Pack\" which occurs after sundown in the slums. This encounter is needed to advance the story.\nThe \"Rieng's Keyring\" mod takes place in the slums. You can get a \"keyring\" which is a container for keys (like a scroll case or gem bag). See &lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.gibberlings3.net/mods/quests/cliffette/\"&gt;A Mod for the Orderly, Download and Readme&lt;/a&gt;. Or go to the wiki gateway page &lt;a href=\"A%20Mod%20for%20the%20Orderly\"&gt;A Mod for the Orderly&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Assassination\"&gt;Assassination&lt;/a&gt; mod has two separate encounters/hit jobs initiated or finished in the slums.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Alternatives\"&gt;Alternatives&lt;/a&gt; mod will have the party approached by a brightly garbed nobleman named \"Malficus\", who offers a passage to an exotic foreign land and a method to take care of Imoen's captivity by the Cowled Wizard's.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod adds various improved and or \"smarter\" AI scripts to various creatures encountered, from dogs, muggers, and all manner of conflicts."}
