{"id": "10024", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10024", "title": "Aura of Despair", "text": "Aura of Despair is an innate special ability usable by &lt;a href=\"Dorn%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Dorn Il-Khan&lt;/a&gt; and player-created &lt;a href=\"Blackguard\"&gt;Blackguard&lt;/a&gt; characters starting at level 3. \nIt is also scripted for use by &lt;a href=\"Anti-Paladin\"&gt;Anti-Paladin&lt;/a&gt; githyanki creatures, especially in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Githyanki%20Encampment\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Githyanki Encampment&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe spell effect is not interruptible and takes 0 seconds time to deploy. The Blackguard casts this ability centered upon oneself. If successful, the ability will inflict the effects described above, with the exception that the damage reduction effect has a limit, as enemies can't be made to do less than 1 damage with it.\nThe ability will affect all enemies (i.e. red-circle creatures, including charmed party members and summoned demons) in a 15' area around the Blackguard, unless it is blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, or the enemy is immune to level 1 spell power area of effect magic, such as a &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rakshasa\"&gt;Rakshasa&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;. The Aura can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity Conjuration&lt;/a&gt; as well.\nThe Aura can be dispelled. \nThe party may be attacked with this spell as it is scripted for use by the &lt;a href=\"Anti-Paladin\"&gt;Anti-Paladin&lt;/a&gt; githyanki blackguards in , examples include during chapter 6 if the player has the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Blade\"&gt;Silver Blade&lt;/a&gt;, and if exploring the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Githyanki%20Encampment\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Githyanki Encampment&lt;/a&gt; when playing the Enhanced Edition."}
{"id": "4772", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4772", "title": "Aura of Flaming Death", "text": "Aura of Flaming Death envelops the caster in an aura of intense flames.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to oneself only.\nWhen the spell is finished, the spell roars to life and renders a 3D graphic effect upon the caster's sprite - a flaming circle of fire, for the spell's duration.\nWhen the spell ends, there is also a sound effect that audibles indicating the expiration of the spell.\nA party member who casts this spell will display an icon (No. 160) titled \"Aura of Flaming Death\" on their portrait.\nThe spell bestows a general 4-point &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; bonus, and immunity to \"non-magical\" weapons/missiles.\nThe flaming aura sets &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance to 90%, which can be modified upwards as high as 127% with other spells, abilities or items that also provide additional fire damage resistance - the exception being that this spell doesn't \"stack\" with itself.\nMost attackers that strike a creature with an active Aura will trigger the spell's retaliatory ability to inflict 2d10+2 fire damage upon the attacker - this damage is applied to the attacker for any and all successful hits (weapon or spell) - for example, a warrior who strikes and hits three times in a single round against the shield will suffer 2d10+2 fire damage three times.\nFor this retaliatory damage effect to occur, the attacker must be close enough to the Aura to trigger it - the spell's description indicates this is a 5 feet range, but in actual practice it is difficult to really see that distance playout exactly during gameplay.\nAttacks that are \"touch\" range, or with melee weapons with a 1-foot range seem to trigger the effect almost always - while attacks with a weapon with a longer reach might not do so reliably.\nSpells and missile weapons launched at near point-blank range can also trigger the retaliatory fire damage.\nThis reach distance trigger can come into play when a large creature, such as a dragon, attacks the flaming Aura - the dragon's sprite \"circle\" is so large that it often won't affect the beast, even if a party member is as close as they can get to the dragon.\nThe Aura's retaliatory damage is unaffected by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, and it isn't deflected/turned by personal spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, but it is blocked by a &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; and \"Spell Ineffective\" is displayed on the combat log. \nThis spell can be removed by any &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect or a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this High-level class ability spell, revising its casting time, duration, effects, and description. See below:\nAura of Flaming Death\nLevel: Quest\nSchool: Evocation\nSphere: Protection, Elemental (Fire)\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 5\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: None\nThis spell causes the caster to be enveloped by an aura of intense flame that both injures opponents and protects from damage. This shield not only grants the user 100% fire resistance and protects him from all non-magical weapons but can also damage creatures within a 5-foot radius around him and enflame weapons held by the caster. Any opponent that hits the caster with a weapon or spell from within this radius suffers 2d10+2 fire damage, and whenever the caster strikes an opponent with a melee weapon, he deals an additional 1d10 points of fire damage."}
{"id": "9328", "revid": "36786428", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9328", "title": "Auril", "text": "Auril, also known as the Frostmaiden, is a &lt;a href=\"neutral%20evil\"&gt;neutral evil&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0lesser &lt;a href=\"deity\"&gt;deity&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0of cold and evil.\nShe is worshipped mostly in northern &lt;a href=\"Faer%C3%BBn\"&gt;Faer\u00fbn&lt;/a&gt; due to its cold climate, usually out of fear rather than adoration.\n&lt;a href=\"Branwen\"&gt;Branwen&lt;/a&gt; mentions Auril in some of her lines."}
{"id": "46537", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46537", "title": "Aurumach Rilmani", "text": "This page is to detail the Aurumach Rilmani guardian creature, a unique tiefling mage that appears in and . \nHe is faced in battle upon using the &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Key\"&gt;Mind Key&lt;/a&gt; upon the eastern pedestal lock on the edge of the Final Seal, in the central chamber of the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; dungeon. \nThis creature is spawned by turning the key, along with five other enemy creatures, the &lt;a href=\"Ferrumach%20Rilmani\"&gt;Ferrumach Rilmani&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe Tiefling creatures rapidly spawn and rise seemingly right out of the stone floor of the main chamber, in a circular spacing around the final seal.\nThis guardian can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;, moves quickly, has several elemental and magical energy damage resistances, and a solid &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; rating.\nAurumach can only by struck by +4 enchanted weapons or greater.\nHis staff confers immunity to level 1 through 4 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; spells and effects, and it also protects against a number of commonly used ammunition projectiles used in missile weapon attacks, such as bolts, darts, bullets, thrown daggers and others.\nAlthough it is a spell caster, the Aurumach can fight with its special quarterstaff as well, and it often casts spells at point blank range and fights in melee combat in the same round.\nThe majority of the creature's spells are rapidly released, and \"ForceSpell\" cast, and thus probably won't be affected by the mage taking damage.\nThe mage uses it's &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt; to perform a potentially devastating attack. During the pause in time, three to five spells with area of effect spread will be launched, so it might affect multiple creatures/party members. \nDuring the Time Stop he will also strike with the enchanted staff.\nThe creature may heal itself completely when its Hit Points are below 30% of original value, but it can only do this once.\nFor a breakdown of the conditions and general triggers used in the mage's AI, see the InfoBox.\nWhen the creature is killed, the corpse disappears from the map, leaving behind only the &lt;a href=\"Club%20of%20Detonation\"&gt;Club of Detonation&lt;/a&gt;, which it never uses in combat.\nBugs.\nThe Aurumach's regeneration ability timing mode is set as permanent, but that setting requires a duration to work, and it has no duration, and therefore it doesn't operate correctly. This is an issue throughout the game in several other creatures as well. This issue is included in &lt;a href=\"The%20Enhanced%20Edition%20Fixpack%20%28EEFP%29\"&gt;The Enhanced Edition Fixpack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt; and is already identified to Beamdog for possible fixing in the future.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod provides this creature with a revised \"smarter\" AI script - capable of recognizing party member protections and vulnerabilities for better tactical behavior.\nThe experience and caster level are raised to 25/25/25.\nSCS retains all the immunities listed in the InfoBox, and adds a few more abilities to Aurumach, including:&lt;br&gt;\n- Immunity to &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;\n- \"Teleport without error\" ability (instantly jump to another point on the map).\nSCS changes use of &lt;a href=\"Symbol%2C%20Fear%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Symbol, Fear (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; and adds &lt;a href=\"Symbol%2C%20Stun%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Symbol, Stun (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Symbol%2C%20Death%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Symbol, Death (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;, and with the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod adds &lt;a href=\"https%3A//gibberlings3.github.io/SpellRevisions/spells/arcane/level-8/symbol-of-weakness\"&gt;Symbol of Weakness&lt;/a&gt;.\nSCS adds use of an innate equivalent of &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; to strip protections from enemies as well."}
