{"id": "9647", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9647", "title": "Avarice", "text": "Avarice is one of four dwarven &lt;a href=\"warders\"&gt;warders&lt;/a&gt; guarding the way to &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Two%29\"&gt;Labyrinth Level Two&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. He must be given the &lt;a href=\"Glittering%20Beljuril%20Gemstone\"&gt;Glittering Beljuril Gemstone&lt;/a&gt; to solve his riddle.\nAvarice has a slight resistance to all elements and magic but can still be caught in spells such as &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt; and affected significantly by offensive magic. His morale is unusually strong and is unlikely to break. He has the ability to cloak at will and does so often; reappearing soon after to &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt; party members. Avarice always casts &lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt; at the start of combat."}
