{"id": "46469", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46469", "title": "Azamantes", "text": "Azamantes will spawn when the &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Key\"&gt;Spirit Key&lt;/a&gt; is turned to unlock the southern pedestal in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; dungeon. Azamantes is a powerful Lich and will be accompanied by three &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Skull\"&gt;Flaming Skull&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nGameplay.\nThe lich and three Flaming Skull allies will rise from the floor in various locations around the Final Seal and initiate hostile actions.\nAzamantes is able to innately &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;.\nAt the outset of appearing in the dungeon, as soon as the lich detects an enemy its initial preparatory protective spell chain is released with &lt;a href=\"Lich%20Fear\"&gt;Lich Fear&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Mantle\"&gt;Improved Mantle&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;.\nFor other spell casting and associated conditions that trigger them, see the InfoBox.\nThe lich's spell triggers, sequencers and contingencies are not generally subject to being disrupted by suffering damage; however other spell casting is fair game.\nAzamantes has some unique damage resistances not normally found on the undead, and fire is one of these - this lich is best destroyed through physical and magical energy damage, although, the creature enjoys a very high &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; rating.\nOf particular note about Azamantes is that the lich cannot adjust his spell casting based on the party's protections (it has very minimal recognition scripting), and it also won't try to dispel or take down the party's spells/buffs. This is quite the limitation for such a high-level spell caster.\nThe lich's &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt; which occurs early in the battle, is probably the most dangerous risk for an opponent - expect an &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment\"&gt;Imprisonment&lt;/a&gt; spell included along with a &lt;a href=\"Meteor%20Swarm\"&gt;Meteor Swarm&lt;/a&gt; and possibly a &lt;a href=\"Abi-Dalzim%27s%20Horrid%20Wilting\"&gt;Abi-Dalzim's Horrid Wilting&lt;/a&gt; all released during the pause in time.\nMod content.\nDepending on the game difficulty selection, the lich will use mage &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; spell casts including &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Alacrity\"&gt;Improved Alacrity&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Breath%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Dragon's Breath (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Comet\"&gt;Comet&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Dark%20Planetar\"&gt;Summon Dark Planetar&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe lich has prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt; ready to deploy instantly.\nExpect a &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wish\"&gt;Wish&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Gate\"&gt;Gate&lt;/a&gt; spells.\nAzamantes can attempt to remove party protections (as it can recognize them) with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Thrust\"&gt;Spell Thrust&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ruby%20Ray%20of%20Reversal\"&gt;Ruby Ray of Reversal&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Khelben%27s%20Warding%20Whip\"&gt;Khelben's Warding Whip&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spellstrike\"&gt;Spellstrike&lt;/a&gt;.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod will change the lich's spell book to the SR versions. This Mod is compatible and designed to work with SCS."}
