{"id": "5286", "revid": "281230", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5286", "title": "Azuredge", "text": "Azuredge is an enchanted throwing axe +3 which returns to the hand of the wielder, and it can be used in melee combat as well. The weapon deals 1d6 points of damage and it has no bonus to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, but the weapon deals 1d6 +4 points of damage to the undead, who must make saving throw with a -4 penalty or be destroyed instantly. This enchantment is similar to the enchantment the &lt;a href=\"Mace%20of%20Disruption\"&gt;Mace of Disruption&lt;/a&gt; has, though it cannot be upgraded to protect against &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nAs of EE 2.5, Azuredge can no longer strike a Demilich, which was a bugfix to correct an unintended behavior. Attempts to strike a creature needing +4 enchantment to hit should display \"Weapon Ineffective\" in the combat screen.\nLocation.\nSold exclusively by &lt;a href=\"Bernard\"&gt;Bernard&lt;/a&gt; in his improved store. \nNote.\nA Neutral Good aligned player character may use this weapon, as long as it meets the class restrictions. The InfoBox default verbiage is unclear in this instance."}
